-> Namespaces are virtual clusters that are backed by the same cluster.

-> k8s objects such as pods and containers, live in namespaces.

-> namespaces helps to organize your objects in your cluster.

-> kubectl get ns

-> incase no ns is specified, kubernetes uses the default ns

-> kubectl get ns ; the two ns we should know better
   - kube-system 
   - default

-> Incase you searching for a pod and you don't remember the ns where it lives
   - kubectl get pods --all-namespaces
